text: Paul Fennell is a male retired British cyclist. ==Cycling career== He represented England in the 10 miles scratch race, the 1 Km time trial and the 4,000 metres team pursuit, at the 1978 Commonwealth Games in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada and was part of the bronze medal pursuit winning team that consisted of Tony James, Tony Doyle and Glen Mitchell. He won one National Championship in 1974. ==References== Category:Living people Category:British male cyclists Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in cycling Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Cyclists at the 1978 Commonwealth Games Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
